Why is this release compressed twice both in zip and rar? Silly if you ask me since it hardly makes the download any smaller, if at all.

Please only include the actual exe and nfo file in upcoming released as it increases the chance of the torrent staying alive longer since people are less likely to delete the excess files and thus reducing the chance of the torrent being seeded for a longer amount of time.

@turbocomppro Relax, it's probably a false positive. Ive had tons of false positives on applications I wrote myself!
NetLimiter is a very "strange" application, messing with very low-level Windows API, so it may be considered dangerous by some AV. Seeing as only one obscure product identified this torrent as "K.gen" is clearly showing that it may contain a KeyGen and nothing more. No reason to be alarmed :)
